summary:
PHOTOS: David Tennant Stars In Episode One Of There She Goes

  The new BBC Four comedy drama There She Goes, stars David...
caption:
PHOTOS: David Tennant Stars In Episode One Of There She Goes

The new BBC Four comedy drama There She Goes, stars David Tennant and Jessica Hynes in the roles of Simon and Emily, the parents of a severely disabled child. The five part comedy drama is based on the real life experiences of writer Simon Pye whose own daughter was born with an as yet undiagnosed chromosomal disorder.

The series continues on BBC Four on Tuesday 23rd October at 10pm BST. Meanwhile you can view the full There She Goes screencap gallery here.

summary: DAY TWO - NYCC, SUNDAY.  nycc time! my first trip into manhattan and i was lucky enough to cross the brooklyn bridge - which was...
caption:
DAY TWO - NYCC, SUNDAY.

nycc time! my first trip into manhattan and i was lucky enough to cross the brooklyn bridge - which was one of my hopes but i couldn’t figure out if i’d be able to do so, as normally drivers use the tunnels. in fact, it was the only time i did cross the bridge, and i filmed it, i’ll post the video in my next post. 

nycc - imagine if you stuffed everyone in the world into one building and dressed a few of them up as batman. it was absolutely jam packed even though it was sunday. you couldn’t move to look at anything or stop to think. the queues for the toilets were insanely long. 

matt smith - i had my photo op with matt smith first and he immediately said ‘oh wow, nice tatts!’ which was lovely of him. he looks so different in real life to how he does on screen - must just have one of those faces. i got to say thank you to him and then it was immediately on to - 

david tennant - his op was much shorter, he just said hi and then we smiled for the camera. he was really full of energy, it radiated off him. 

after that, i wanted to go to artist alley, which was just rammed with people. i wanted to find something captain america related, i just didn’t realise the prices would be so insane. i saw original pieces selling for $6,000 - which i’m sure is what they’re worth, but i’d brought $350 for the whole trip, so. our price ranges were a little out. i did find an amazing foil print of cap and bucky (original bucky) standing over a bunch of dead nazis (the only good nazi is a dead nazi) and it’s really beautiful, so i bought that. 

the streets outside the con, for blocks and blocks, were crowded with people dressed up and it was very difficult to try move and get around. my anxiety was spiking pretty badly after everything.

we went back to the airbnb, going through the tunnel this time.

i would recommend nycc for the experience, but not if you’re not great with crowds or if you want to be able to actually see or do anything. the disability staff however couldn’t do enough for you - they were so kind and in fact, i found during my stay americans are so much nicer than brits. 


PLEASE DO NOT EDIT, CROP, REDISTRIBUTE OR OTHERWISE ALTER THESE PHOTO OP IMAGES, THANK YOU.
